---
layout: base.njk
title: "About — Harry Wellbelove"
description: "About Harry Wellbelove — Cyber Security Professional. SC Cleared."
permalink: /about/
---

<main style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;">
<div class="wrap page-content" style="padding-top:calc(var(--nav-h) + 48px);padding-bottom:16px;flex:1;display:flex;flex-direction:column;">

  <section class="section fade-in" style="margin-bottom:48px;">
    <div style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:0.18em;color:var(--dim);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:16px;">About</div>
    <h1 class="display-lg" style="margin-bottom:32px;">
      Who I <em class="accent">am.</em>
    </h1>

    <div>
      <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.8;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:20px;">
        I started in cyber straight out of college at a two-person SOC, triaging around 2,000 alerts
        a month across finance, education, and energy customers on a week-on/week-off on-call rota.
        There's no gentle introduction to the industry when it's just you and one other person —
        you learn fast or you fall behind.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.8;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:20px;">
        I joined Meridian IT in 2023 to build the managed SOC service from scratch — KQL detections,
        runbooks, reporting templates, the lot. A year in I took over as the senior escalation point,
        then jumped across to the engineering side for about 16 months to work on a greenfield
        CNI programme for a UK energy operator. End of 2025 I came back to the SOC as Manager and
        inherited a team of five.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.8;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:20px;">
        The engineering detour was deliberate. I care about knowing how systems are actually put
        together, not just watching telemetry from them — you can't detect what you don't understand,
        and the best SOC work I've seen comes from people who know the infrastructure well enough to
        predict where it'll break.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.8;text-align:justify;">
        Outside of that — home lab, bike, too many side projects. I run a three-node Proxmox/Ceph
        cluster at home that mirrors the kit I work with professionally, mainly so I can break things
        without bricking a client environment. I also do the 300-in-30 cycling challenge for Cancer
        Research every June. If my legs hurt, it's probably that.
      </p>
    </div>

  </section>

  <section class="section fade-in-2" style="margin-bottom:48px;">
    <div style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:0.18em;color:var(--dim);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:20px;">Journey</div>

    <div style="position:relative;padding-left:24px;border-left:1px solid var(--rule);">

      {% set journey = [
        { dates: "Dec 2025 — Now", title: "SOC Manager", company: "Meridian IT", blurb: "Redesigned the SOC operating model and commercial framework. Leading a team of five across a regulated customer estate.", current: true },
        { dates: "Aug 2024 — Dec 2025", title: "Cyber Security Engineer", company: "Meridian IT", blurb: "Greenfield CNI programme on behalf of a UK energy operator — CIS Level 2 hardening, OPNsense HA firewall pairs, internal PKI, out-of-band management, full SAT sign-off against NCSC CAF and NIST CSF." },
        { dates: "Feb 2024 — Aug 2024", title: "Senior Cyber Security Analyst", company: "Meridian IT", blurb: "Sole operational ownership of the managed SOC. Built the detection runbook library, trained junior analysts, moved a regulated finance customer onto Recorded Future." },
        { dates: "Feb 2023 — Feb 2024", title: "Cyber Security Analyst", company: "Meridian IT", blurb: "Built the managed SOC service from scratch — detection queries, runbooks, reporting templates. Scaled across finance and education customers." },
        { dates: "Feb 2021 — Feb 2023", title: "Cyber Security Analyst", company: "CyberFit Security", blurb: "First role out of college. Two-person SOC, ~2,000 alerts a month across finance, education, and energy. Week-on/week-off on-call throughout." }
      ] %}

      {% for role in journey %}
      <div style="position:relative;padding-bottom:28px;">
        <div style="position:absolute;left:-30px;top:6px;width:11px;height:11px;border-radius:50%;background:{% if role.current %}var(--accent){% else %}var(--s2){% endif %};border:2px solid var(--bg);box-shadow:0 0 0 1px var(--rule);"></div>
        <div style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:var(--dim);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:6px;">{{ role.dates }}</div>
        <div style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:2px;">{{ role.title }}</div>
        <div style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11px;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:8px;">{{ role.company }}</div>
        <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.7;">{{ role.blurb }}</p>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section fade-in-3" style="margin-bottom:48px;">
    <div style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:0.18em;color:var(--dim);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:20px;">Certifications</div>

    <div style="display:grid;gap:8px;">

      {% set certs = [
        { name: "CISSP", issuer: "ISC2", year: "In progress", pending: true },
        { name: "SC-200 · Security Operations Analyst Associate", issuer: "Microsoft", year: "2021" },
        { name: "Google Cybersecurity Professional Certificate", issuer: "Coursera", year: "2023" },
        { name: "Jira Fundamentals", issuer: "Atlassian", year: "2024" },
        { name: "L3 Extended Diploma · Computer Science", issuer: "Milton Keynes College", year: "2021" }
      ] %}

      {% for cert in certs %}
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:16px;padding:14px 16px;background:var(--s1);border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:var(--radius-lg);">
        <div style="min-width:0;flex:1;">
          <div style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:12px;font-weight:500;color:var(--ink);line-height:1.3;margin-bottom:2px;">{{ cert.name }}</div>
          <div style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:10px;color:var(--dim);">{{ cert.issuer }}</div>
        </div>
        <div style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:{% if cert.pending %}var(--accent){% else %}var(--dim){% endif %};text-transform:uppercase;flex-shrink:0;">{{ cert.year }}</div>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section fade-in-4" style="margin-top:auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:24px;flex-wrap:wrap;padding:24px 28px;background:var(--s1);border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:var(--radius-lg);">
    <div>
      <div style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:20px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:6px;">
        If you've got something worth <em class="accent">talking about.</em>
      </div>
      <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);">Get in touch directly or via the contact page.</div>
    </div>
    <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/contact/">Get in touch →</a>
  </section>

</div>
</main>
